# CP Crime — HRDS Internal Endpoints
# Spec: https://app.swaggerhub.com/apis/HMCTS-DTS/api-cp-crime-hearing-results-document-subscription — v2.0.9
#
# ⚠  INTERNAL USE ONLY — these endpoints trigger upstream workflows and should NOT
#    be run as part of normal API testing. They exist for local integration testing
#    when the upstream event pipeline is not available.
#
# Works in: IntelliJ HTTP Client · VS Code REST Client · httpyac CLI
# Select environment: hrds-dev | hrds-sit | hrds-preprod | hrds-prod
#
# Prerequisites:
#   1. Run "Get Entra Access Token" in hrds.http first (sets hrds_access_token globally).
#   2. Run "Create a client subscription" in hrds.http (sets client_subscription_id globally),
#      or set client_subscription_id manually in your env file.

# VS Code: resolves token from hrds.http named request
@hrds_access_token = {{getHrdsToken.response.body.$.access_token}}

###

# ─── Notifications ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# POST /notifications triggers document generation and delivers a webhook to the
# registered callbackUrl. Returns HTTP 202 (empty body) — document_id is NOT
# available from the response; it arrives via the webhook callback.

# @name createNotification
### Create a notification (triggers document generation)
POST {{hrds_base_url}}/notifications
Authorization: Bearer {{hrds_access_token}}
Ocp-Apim-Subscription-Key: {{hrds_subscription_key}}
Content-Type: application/json
X-Correlation-Id: d679fd61-061f-4440-9623-36280f0807b7

{
  "eventId": "3fa85f64-5717-4562-b3fc-2c963f66afa6",
  "materialId": "123e4567-e89b-12d3-a456-426614174000",
  "eventType": "PRISON_COURT_REGISTER_GENERATED",
  "timestamp": "2024-01-15T10:30:00Z",
  "defendant": {
    "masterDefendantId": "8b8f1c3a-9a41-4f0f-b8a0-1c23d9e8a111",
    "name": "John Doe",
    "dateOfBirth": "1990-05-15",
    "custodyEstablishmentDetails": {
      "emailAddress": "prison@moj.gov.uk"
    },
    "cases": [
      { "urn": "CT98KRYCAP" },
      { "urn": "AB75123123" }
    ]
  }
}

###
